    <open-items-for-downstream>
      <item task="051">
        Multi-tab same-user conflict UX. The existing endpoint returns 200 (NOT 409) for same-user re-checkout per DocumentCheckoutService.CheckoutAsync line 121-152. Task 051 must therefore use a separate detection mechanism — likely a checkout-status probe (GET /api/documents/{id}/checkout-status) on mount that compares CheckoutUserInfo.Id to the current user's Dataverse systemuserid. The current 050 implementation lands same-user multi-tab in the 'acquired' state with no warning; 051 replaces that with the richer "Go-to-other / Force-close" modal per spike §1 row 4.
      </item>
      <item task="052">
        Heartbeat sweeper BFF backend. Client-side heartbeat already exists in W4-045 ComposeEditor (3-min sliding, visibility-gated). Task 052 must add: (a) RefreshHeartbeatAsync method on existing DocumentCheckoutService, (b) POST /api/compose/document/{documentId}/heartbeat endpoint, (c) StaleCheckoutSweeperHostedService for 15-min orphan release, (d) sprk_lastheartbeatutc field (already created per W1a OI-2). All per Spike #3 §4.3.
      </item>
      <item task="041 ComposeDocumentRef">
        The current effect uses state.documentRef.sprkDocumentId which is typed as optional per ComposeDocumentRef (compose-contracts.ts task 041). No new type required — leverage existing contract.
      </item>
    </open-items-for-downstream>
